11 Section 1. Section 61-4-123, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "61-4-123. Dealer requirements and restrictions. (1) A used dealer may not sell a new motor
13 vehicle, a new power sports vehicle, or a new trailer.
14 (2) A dealer may not display at the dealer's established place of business or any approved off-
15 premises sale location a motor vehicle offered for sale, trade, or consignment unless the Monroney label
16 required for new motor vehicles pursuant to 15 U.S.C. 1232 or the buyer's guide label required for used motor
17 vehicles pursuant to 16 CFR, part 455, is affixed to the side window of the motor vehicle or is conspicuously
18 displayed within the motor vehicle in a fashion that is readily readable by a customer.
19 (3) (a) Except as provided in subsection (4), a dealer may not sell or display a motor vehicle,
20 power sports vehicle, or trailer offered for sale at any geographic location other than that of the dealer's
21 established place of business as listed on the dealer's license.
22 (b) A dealer may park a motor vehicle in a storage lot if:
23 (i) local zoning regulations permit that type of use;
24 (ii) the lot is in the county where the dealer's established place of business is located;
25 (iii) the dealer does not sell or advertise the sale of the motor vehicle at the lot; and
26 (iv) if applicable, the placement of the motor vehicle complies with the dealer's franchise
27 agreement.
28 (4) (a) Upon On prior notice to the department, a dealer may conduct an off-premises display and
