19 obligation imposed under chapter 6 of this title.
20 (9) A dealer shall display at the dealer's established place of business at least one sign stating the
21 name of the business and indicating that motor vehicles, power sports vehicles, or trailers are offered for sale,
22 trade, or consignment. The letters of the sign must be at least 6 inches in height and clearly visible and
23 readable to the major avenue of traffic at a minimum distance of 150 feet.
24 (10) As used in this section, "motor vehicle" means:
25 (a) a recreational vehicle as defined in 61-1-101(61);
26 (b) a motorboat and a personal watercraft as defined in 23-2-502;
