2 SECTION 2. SECTION 61-4-201, MCA, IS AMENDED TO READ:
3 "61-4-201. Definitions. As used in this part, the following definitions apply unless the context clearly
4 indicates otherwise:
5 (1) "Community" means the relevant market area of a franchise. For the purposes of this part, the
6 relevant market area of a franchise is the county or counties in which the franchisee is located.
7 (2) "Distribute" means to sell new motor vehicles other than at retail or to enter into a franchise
8 agreement authorizing a dealer to buy new motor vehicles for resale or to service motor vehicles under a
9 manufacturer's or distributor's warranty.
10 (3) "Distributor" or "wholesaler" means a person who sells or distributes a line-make of new motor
11 vehicles to new motor vehicle dealers in this state or who maintains distributor representatives in this state.
12 (4) "Distributor branch" means a branch office maintained or availed of by a distributor or
13 wholesaler for the sale of a line-make of new motor vehicles to new motor vehicle dealers in this state for
14 directing or supervising its representatives in this state.
15 (5) "Factory branch" means a branch office maintained or availed of by a manufacturer for the sale
16 of a line-make of new motor vehicles to distributors or for the sale of new motor vehicles to new motor vehicle
17 dealers in this state or for directing or supervising its representatives in this state.
18 (6) "Franchise" means a contract and any agreed-to amendments between or among two or more
19 persons when all of the following conditions are included:
20 (a) a commercial relationship of definite duration or continuing indefinite duration is involved;
21 (b) the franchisee is granted the right to:
22 (i) offer, sell, and service in this state new motor vehicles manufactured or distributed by the
23 franchisor; or
24 (ii) service motor vehicles pursuant to the terms of a franchise and a manufacturer's warranty;
25 (c) the franchisee, as an independent and separate business, constitutes a component of the
26 franchisor's distribution system; and
27 (d) the operation of the franchisee's business is substantially reliant on the franchisor for the
28 continued supply of new motor vehicles, parts, and accessories.
